: "Do_historians_and_human_scientists_have_an_ethical_obligation_to_follow_the_dire.application/pdf", "fileType": "application/pdf", "pageCount": 3, "uploadedAt": "2026-02-13T07:57:38.330Z", "expiresAt": "2026-02-15T07:57:36.091Z"}], "feedback": [{"versionId": "adaf74e5-fe69-4ff5-865a-211ee928f7ba", "criterionId": "e708a9f2-1aa2-48b1-8848-2655ed338b08", "score": 8, "strengths": ["Sustained, explicit engagement with the prescribed title throughout the essay.", "Purposeful, effective use of well-chosen contemporary and historical case studies to ground abstract discussion.", "Clear, coherent arguments that draw explicit implications for policy, public understanding, and collective memory.", "Strong evaluative balance, with alternative perspectives acknowledged and weighed thoughtfully."], "weaknesses": ["The notion of an \u00e2\u0080\u009cethical obligation\u00e2\u0080\u009d and the threshold for \u00e2\u0080\u009csufficient\u00e2\u0080\u009d contradictory evidence remain only loosely defined.", "Dense sentence structures at times hamper clarity and the flow of the argument.", "Transitions between human sciences and historical examples could be more explicitly linked to improve coherence.", "Analytical precision could be enhanced by distinguishing isolated outliers from systematic counterexamples more clearly."], "calculationMethod": "Holistic AI evaluation: The essay demonstrates performance in the 9\u00e2\u0080\u009310 band through sustained focus on the title, effective links to areas of knowledge, strong examples and higher-order evaluation of different viewpoints. However, minor limitations\u00e2\u0080\u0094such as loosely defined normative concepts, occasional lapses in clarity, and more precise analytical distinctions\u00e2\u0080\u0094prevent it from achieving the topmost mark. Given the examiner\u00e2\u0080\u0099s final total of 8 and the essay\u00e2\u0080\u0099s very strong but not flawless performance, a criterion score of 8 appropriately reflects its overall quality.", "groupName": "TOK Essay"}], "strandSelections": [{"versionId": "adaf74e5-fe69-4ff5-865a-211ee928f7ba", "strandId": "8dc05406-c8b4-4575-8c75-4290cad64660", "selectedBandId": "75fe47cc-47c7-49eb-b495-91b658124b36", "bandScore": 9, "reasoning": "$49"}], "annotations": [{"id": "fcee7c5a-1d5e-49e1-a665-739bd14c9b1e", "versionId": "adaf74e5-fe69-4ff5-865a-211ee928f7ba", "criterionId": "e708a9f2-1aa2-48b1-8848-2655ed338b08", "strandId": null, "type": "strength", "pageNumber": 1, "bbox": {"x": 0.0805, "y": 0.1046, "width": 0.844, "height": 0.1973}, "polygon": [{"x": 0.0805, "y": 0.1046}, {"x": 0.9245, "y": 0.1046}, {"x": 0.9245, "y": 0.3019}, {"x": 0.0805, "y": 0.3019}], "comment": "The introduction offers a clear, precise definition of \u00e2\u0080\u009cignoring contradictory evidence\u00e2\u0080\u009d in both history and the human sciences, setting a strong conceptual foundation and demonstrating purposeful engagement with the prescribed title.", "color": null, "status": "unread", "statusUpdatedAt": null, "statusUpdatedBy": null, "groupName": "TOK Essay"}, {"id": "9a397182-6b0c-4542-aef4-2d1ec98e5677", "versionId": "adaf74e5-fe69-4ff5-865a-211ee928f7ba", "criterionId": "e708a9f2-1aa2-48b1-8848-2655ed338b08", "strandId": null, "type": "weakness", "pageNumber": 1, "bbox": {"x": 0.0805, "y": 0.3139, "width": 0.844, "height": 0.317}, "polygon": [{"x": 0.0805, "y": 0.3139}, {"x": 0.9245, "y": 0.3139}, {"x": 0.9245, "y": 0.6309}, {"x": 0.0805, "y": 0.6309}], "comment": "When citing Kahneman and Tversky versus Henrich et al., the essay could better evaluate the methodological limitations of WEIRD samples by explaining how cross-cultural studies challenge assumptions and what this implies for generalizability.", "color": null, "status": "unread", "statusUpdatedAt": null, "statusUpdatedBy": null, "groupName": "TOK Essay"}, {"id": "6ac1be25-b14f-4488-b04a-df3813e0e532", "versionId": "adaf74e5-fe69-4ff5-865a-211ee928f7ba", "criterionId": "e708a9f2-1aa2-48b1-8848-2655ed338b08", "strandId": null, "type": "strength", "pageNumber": 1, "bbox": {"x": 0.0805, "y": 0.3139, "width": 0.844, "height": 0.317}, "polygon": [{"x": 0.0805, "y": 0.3139}, {"x": 0.9245, "y": 0.3139}, {"x": 0.9245, "y": 0.6309}, {"x": 0.0805, "y": 0.6309}], "comment": "The microfinance example effectively illustrates ethical consequences of ignoring contradictory behavioral data, anchoring abstract discussion in a concrete policy failure that highlights real-world stakes.", "color": null, "status": "unread", "statusUpdatedAt": null, "statusUpdatedBy": null, "groupName": "TOK Essay"}, {"id": "2d3ccfed-be0e-49b2-b457-c9d60a7fb72c", "versionId": "adaf74e5-fe69-4ff5-865a-211ee928f7ba", "criterionId": "e708a9f2-1aa2-48b1-8848-2655ed338b08", "strandId": null, "type": "weakness", "pageNumber": 2, "bbox": {"x": 0.0818, "y": 0.1046, "width": 0.844, "height": 0.2872}, "polygon": [{"x": 0.0818, "y": 0.1046}, {"x": 0.9258, "y": 0.1046}, {"x": 0.9258, "y": 0.3918}, {"x": 0.0818, "y": 0.3918}], "comment": "The transition from human sciences to historical examples would benefit from an explicit linking sentence that reiterates how both disciplines negotiate simplification versus completeness, improving coherence.", "color": null, "status": "unread", "statusUpdatedAt": null, "statusUpdatedBy": null, "groupName": "TOK Essay"}, {"id": "137e98ce-e871-4c62-88dc-ca80903bf717", "versionId": "adaf74e5-fe69-4ff5-865a-211ee928f7ba", "criterionId": "e708a9f2-1aa2-48b1-8848-2655ed338b08", "strandId": null, "type": "weakness", "pageNumber": 1, "bbox": {"x": 0.0805, "y": 0.1046, "width": 0.844, "height": 0.1973}, "polygon": [{"x": 0.0805, "y": 0.1046}, {"x": 0.9245, "y": 0.1046}, {"x": 0.9245, "y": 0.3019}, {"x": 0.0805, "y": 0.3019}], "comment": "The discussion of contradictory evidence in the human sciences conflates anomalies with inherent variability; the student should distinguish between isolated outliers and systematic counterexamples to strengthen the analytical precision.", "color": null, "status": "unread", "statusUpdatedAt": null, "statusUpdatedBy": null, "groupName": "TOK Essay"}, {"id": "84ec3e7f-08eb-4edf-9e17-28cfa6e7093b", "versionId": "adaf74e5-fe69-4ff5-865a-211ee928f7ba", "criterionId": "e708a9f2-1aa2-48b1-8848-2655ed338b08", "strandId": null, "type": "weakness", "pageNumber": 1, "bbox": {"x": 0.0805, "y": 0.3139, "width": 0.844, "height": 0.317}, "polygon": [{"x": 0.0805, "y": 0.3139}, {"x": 0.9245, "y": 0.3139}, {"x": 0.9245, "y": 0.6309}, {"x": 0.0805, "y": 0.6309}], "comment": "To deepen the critique of microfinance models, the student should consider structural economic factors in addition to behavioural biases, ensuring a more balanced evaluation of policy failure.", "color": null, "status": "unread", "statusUpdatedAt": null, "statusUpdatedBy": null, "groupName": "TOK Essay"}, {"id": "ff18aaa7-0060-4540-ab0b-56e3d5b3d21a", "versionId": "adaf74e5-fe69-4ff5-865a-211ee928f7ba", "criterionId": "e708a9f2-1aa2-48b1-8848-2655ed338b08", "strandId": null, "type": "strength", "pageNumber": 2, "bbox": {"x": 0.0818, "y": 0.1046, "width": 0.844, "height": 0.2872}, "polygon": [{"x": 0.0818, "y": 0.1046}, {"x": 0.9258, "y": 0.1046}, {"x": 0.9258, "y": 0.3918}, {"x": 0.0818, "y": 0.3918}], "comment": "The historiographical debate over Virginia\u00e2\u0080\u0099s slave codes is well chosen and the comparison of economic versus racial explanations shows clear evaluation of competing perspectives.", "color": null, "status": "unread", "statusUpdatedAt": null, "statusUpdatedBy": null, "groupName": "TOK Essay"}, {"id": "f3d1f63e-f951-4b95-bac9-e0be4d4654c7", "versionId": "adaf74e5-fe69-4ff5-865a-211ee928f7ba", "criterionId": "e708a9f2-1aa2-48b1-8848-2655ed338b08", "strandId": null, "type": "weakness", "pageNumber": 1, "bbox": {"x": 0.0805, "y": 0.6447, "width": 0.8452999999999999, "height": 0.2849999999999999}, "polygon": [{"x": 0.0805, "y": 0.6447}, {"x": 0.9258, "y": 0.6447}, {"x": 0.9258, "y": 0.9297}, {"x": 0.0805, "y": 0.9297}], "comment": "The argument for ignoring contradictory evidence in public health messaging invokes ethical duties but lacks explicit reference to ethical frameworks; linking to consequentialist or deontological principles would clarify the normative basis of these claims.", "color": null, "status": "unread", "statusUpdatedAt": null, "statusUpdatedBy": null, "groupName": "TOK Essay"}, {"id": "57db2b46-48d8-4d21-b7db-d96b1d465723", "versionId": "adaf74e5-fe69-4ff5-865a-211ee928f7ba", "criterionId": "e708a9f2-1aa2-48b1-8848-2655ed338b08", "strandId": null, "type": "strength", "pageNumber": 1, "bbox": {"x": 0.0805, "y": 0.6447, "width": 0.8452999999999999, "height": 0.2849999999999999}, "polygon": [{"x": 0.0805, "y": 0.6447}, {"x": 0.9258, "y": 0.6447}, {"x": 0.9258, "y": 0.9297}, {"x": 0.0805, "y": 0.9297}], "comment": "The critical engagement with Matthew Walker\u00e2\u0080\u0099s Why We Sleep and Guzey\u00e2\u0080\u0099s critique demonstrates strong awareness of how communication choices can selectively omit evidence, enriching the TOK analysis of knowledge dissemination.", "color": null, "status": "unread", "statusUpdatedAt": null, "statusUpdatedBy": null, "groupName": "TOK Essay"}, {"id": "ea98d7ce-72fe-4acc-9d1a-acb10d97d2dd", "versionId": "adaf74e5-fe69-4ff5-865a-211ee928f7ba", "criterionId": "e708a9f2-1aa2-48b1-8848-2655ed338b08", "strandId": null, "type": "weakness", "pageNumber": 2, "bbox": {"x": 0.0818, "y": 0.1046, "width": 0.844, "height": 0.2872}, "polygon": [{"x": 0.0818, "y": 0.1046}, {"x": 0.9258, "y": 0.1046}, {"x": 0.9258, "y": 0.3918}, {"x": 0.0818, "y": 0.3918}], "comment": "To strengthen the Virginia case study, the student should integrate specific dates and primary source quotations, which would ground the narrative and illustrate how evidence selection shapes interpretation.", "color": null, "status": "unread", "statusUpdatedAt": null, "statusUpdatedBy": null, "groupName": "TOK Essay"}, {"id": "27d7e350-a45a-4725-a482-b6cd05a1ca07", "versionId": "adaf74e5-fe69-4ff5-8